[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Maybe you\'ve recently come across Gaussian Splatting and have been starting to wonder, "Okay, is this technology actually going to be used out in the real world?" And the answer to that question is it actually has been used in a lot more places than you might think. So, in today\'s video, I\'m going to walk you through some of the industries where Gaussian Splatting is'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'already showing up in production. And some of these examples you may have already seen before, so I tried to include a couple that perhaps I don\'t think as many people are aware of, especially on the dynamic side. And originally, this video was supposed to just be the top five uses of Gaussian'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Splatting so far, but as I actually started to compile the list, I realized that it\'s not feasible. There\'s too many. So, we\'re just going to go ahead, we\'re going to get into it. We\'re going to start with the first industry, which is media and entertainment. Going back to 2022, before Gaussian Splatting even'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'exists, we were seeing radiance fields already show up in music videos. You know, artists like Zayn Malik, Earl Sweatshirt, Chris Brown, Polo G, and Usher, they were all using NeRFs. And now with Gaussian Splatting, this trend'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'has only expanded in scope. The most recent example of which was A$AP Rocky\'s music video for Helicopter, in which almost every person is dynamic Gaussian Splatting, which is otherwise known as 4D GS. It was everywhere the week it came out. Somebody posted the article I'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wrote about the project and it went to number one on Hacker News that same day. Grin Machine and Evercoast shot the music video and then brought it into Houdini using G Sops and then into OTOY\'s Octane Render. UK-based artist Tinie Tempah has also been using dynamic'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Gaussian Splatting in his music videos. And then there\'s also film. You\'re probably aware at this point that Gaussian Splatting played a significant role in the Superman movie, but in case you\'re not, every single shot of Superman\'s parents in the film is dynamic Gaussian Splatting, which was'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'captured by Infinite Realities and the VFX work being done by Framestore. Infinite Realities is the same company I did a 4D GS demo with back in 2024, and I actually interviewed the Framestore team about how they actually went about the process. But if you couldn\'t tell'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that those shots were traditional 2D, me either. And that kind of was the point. It already was so visually strong that we don\'t know it\'s not 2D anymore. If you\'re a fan of red carpet events, you might be familiar with the Glambot and have been wondering when Gaussian'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Splatting will make its way onto the red carpet, too. But the BAFTAs just used Gaussian Splatting at their awards back in February and it wasn\'t the first time. They\'ve actually used Gaussian Splatting three times already across the past two years with the capturing being'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'done by Harry Nelder and team who is going to be popping up a few times in this video. Another recent project they just completed was Amazon Music UK\'s award show and you can see a whole bunch of splats if you go through their'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Instagram. Another big adopter of Gaussian Splatting has been pre-production for film and TV. Back in October I spoke to the team at Ready VFX who used Gaussian Splatting to prepare for season 1 of Dune: Prophecy and they were so stoked about the results that'

[02:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'they were getting where they were using captures to better plan out shots. If we take a look at more of the film side, Proof Inc. used Gaussian Splatting on Jurassic World: Rebirth during pre-visualization to allow the director Gareth Edwards to more freely move about'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the reconstructions using a virtual camera and better plan the shots before anyone even showed up there. You might not have known this one, but Sinners actually used Gaussian Splatting for the avatar of Michael B. Jordan\'s character and they utilized 10 action cams from'

[02:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'something that they called the Halo rig. But, yes, no, they are actually using Gaussian Splatting to power the very lifelike reconstructions of him. And there are many more films that have used Gaussian Splatting on set that I can\'t'

[03:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'show just yet, but I will cover them as they release. So, if you are also a VFX supervisor or are also using Gaussian Splatting on set for your own project, please reach out to me. Sports deserve their own section here mainly because I'

